For example, the experts debate when the lizards split into their three main lines of development: the carnivorous theropods, which later included the tyrannosaurus rex, the Velociraptor and also the birds known as "long-hauls", the four-legged saprods and their relatives, and the plants eating ornithischia (vogelbucken aquariums), which included, for example, the species Triceratops and stegosaurus.
After the analysis of Nesbitt and his colleagues, Tawa hallae is an original theropode.
He has an interesting combination of primitive and progressive properties, says Nesbitt.
On the skull of Tawa hallae, for example, the researchers found indications of airbags, as they also have the descendants of the Theropods, the birds.
Thanks to the airbags, the breathing of the birds is more efficient than that of the mammals.
At Tawa hallae the bones of the spine were apparently partly filled with air.
Tawa is the oldest and most primitive theropod with airbags, says Randall Irmis.
Since the related line of the huge Sauropods later also had airbags and lightweight construction bones, probably the joint ancestor of both groups had already produced this useful innovation.
At least three migration waves to North America
Because the most primitive dinosaurs so far lived in South America, the researchers conclude that the lizards appeared there for the first time.
