In last October, the Group of Solera Autoonline bought a flatfome on the Internet for the sale of accident vehicles and motorcycles.
This purchase meant the payment of €59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could increase to the remaining 15% next year.
The purpose of this purchase was to offer its customers more services and value increase, with the possibility of gaining access to a huge international market.
This assessment and purchase service is exclusively addressed to professionals, such as insurance companies, experts, car rental companies, workshops, scrapyards and car dealers, who have to register before their activities.
This platform was founded in Germany in 1996 and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, 500,000 of which alone in Germany.
Their main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The website today has more than 1,500 registered sellers and 4,000 reviewers.
Every day 3,000 ads are managed and 100 new ads are added to the Spanish market every day.
According to the Spanish legislation, a vehicle whose vehicle number has been registered may no longer drive on the roads, but certain non-damaged parts may be used as spare parts.
The cars with historical value may, on the other hand, be re-approved even if they have been signed off after difficult official tours.
Four-step estimate of the workshop’s costs
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps:Identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
The easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince older professionals who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road cars, 137 motorcycles, 78 small vehicles and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with Internet connection to use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified using the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and after that the spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for hours, surcharges or discounts, and then he can print out the cost estimate and pass it on to his customer.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool to assess such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount that the customer can pay without further delay.
At the moment, the company Audatex is working on being able to offer these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that auto mechanics have been waiting for a long time, because you can choose a door with it for example and then turn the image completely to look at the inside.
